      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index validation — full operating envelope with Monte Carlo UQ",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-in-vitro",
      "description": "The hemolysis index validation was conducted across all five flow-speed combinations specified in the COU. In-vitro hemolysis measurements were performed using bovine blood with standardized ASTM F1841 protocols at an ISO 17025-accredited haematology laboratory. The modified index of haemolysis (MIH) was computed from plasma-free haemoglobin measurements taken at 15-minute intervals over a 6-hour recirculation period. CFD predictions of the scalar transport hemolysis model (power-law formulation, Giersiepen coefficients) were post-processed using the same MIH formula applied to Lagrangian particle tracks seeded uniformly at the inlet. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (n=2000 samples) was applied to the six most sensitive input parameters identified by global Sobol sensitivity analysis: inlet flow rate, rotational speed, blood viscosity, hemolysis model exponent alpha, hemolysis model exponent beta, and linear damage accumulation threshold. The 95th-percentile prediction interval was compared against the experimental mean ± 2 SD band. Agreement was assessed using the U95 validation metric per ASME V&V 20. At all five operating points the CFD 95th-percentile prediction remained below the absolute clinical hemolysis threshold of 0.8 g/dL/100 mL. The validation campaign was executed between January and March 2024 by the computational haemodynamics group; raw simulation outputs, particle track files, and post-processing scripts are archived in the project repository under tag v3.2.1."
    }
